                  </persName>
             (Police-constable F 126). I was on duty in Brook-street, Holborn, on the 26th of July, about seven o'clock in the evening, and saw Hudson coming into a public-house, with this tea-chest in a bag, and Saunders with him; Hudson wished to leave the bag, but the landlord would not let him; I asked what it was, and Hudson said it was no business of mine - I took them to the watch-house, and then Hudson said, it was a tea-chest which he bought in Tottenham court-road, for 12s.; they were about three hundred yards from the prosecutors'.</p>
               <p>Saunders. Q. Where was I? A. You were coming in just behind him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-294-person2434">
                  ROBERT 
                  LYON
               <interp inst="t18320906-294-person2434" type="surname" value="LYON"></interp>
