             (Police-constable F 35). On the 26th of July, between one and two o'clock, I saw the prisoners in Holborn - I watched them; they went into an optician's; they then went to the prosecutors', and from there to the public-house where they were taken; they had changed coats after I saw them.</p>
               <p>Hudson's Defence. I saw a man with this and some others, and he wanted 16s. for one - I offered him 12s.; he would not take it - I walked away; he ran after me and let me have it - I then went to the Three Tuns with it, and was taken.</p>
               <p>Saunders' Defence. I was in the tap-room when Hudson came in - I had not seen him before.</p>
